text.__SUMMARY__: Dendrobium sanguinolentum, the blood-stained dendrobium, is a species of flowering plant in the family Orchidaceae. It is native to Southeast Asia (Thailand, Malaysia, Philippines, Borneo, Java, Sumatra).
